		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Birthday beatdown in Garden Grove, CA<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.80)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=3656'>John "Patch" Patchell</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=3656&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> August 26, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> On Friday, I drive out to Fontana to pick up my boy David &#8220;Databoy&#8221; Tru&#8212;Deau!  He&#8217;s gonna help me out for two big events Ive been planning for a while. The first is Ram Deleons tournament out at Mile High Comics in Garden Grove. This was Ram&#8217;s first shot at directing and I wanted to be there to support him.  Also, mile high is a good group in general for LOTR.  But, secondly and more important was my birthday party!!! I was turning the big 3-0 on Sunday and we were gonna celebrate on Sat night.  So Tru- Deau and I roll down to Staters to buy some groceries and what not for the party (as everyone knows though, card players are flaky, so I couldn&#8217;t trust them to bring food &#8211;even though its my birthday!!&#8212;plus I didn&#8217;t know how many would actually show up). My man Mark Evans had already dropped off some steaks and chairs, so I picked up some dogs and burgers and other goodies, all tolled it was like $70!  Well, Tru-Deau and I were unsatisfied with the selection of cake and ice cream, so we roll to Ralph&#8217;s and find some good stuff there.  So the shopping is all done for the party.  Now, I just have to prepare for the event itself.  <br />
	I have two decks that I like.  One is the Gandalf Aragorn Signet Small fellowship/Nazgul bb bt that I ran the week before, the other is a super fellowship/ uruks that mike Kessling sent me (yes, the same guy who rated my stuff 1s with no unction, Comic con has made us fast friends, and I hope mike will review this highly, to make up for those 1s).  I played the Gandalf one at league night at mile high the night before so I don&#8217;t want to run it. The Uruk deck won every play test I did with it, and it did it smoothly. Both decks run Anduin confluence, so I am glad for that cause I&#8217;m sick of horn domination.  The super fellowship is a good call cause many people have started to run moria and nazgul again, but in playtest, this deck also beat uruks!  The deck is a tight 64 cards.  It starts with friend of the shire folk and green dragon. <br />
	Tru-Deau and I stay up till for and I reset my alarm several times. Mike Garland wakes me up and we get ready to go.  Dunya Ertan is supposed to meet us there.  The rest of my squad, too lazy to get up early,  (the tourney is twelve) are going to Pasadena (see Lisa ganskys tr).  Teddy  T, you&#8217;re forgiven of course.  <br />
	We roll out to Mile High and have 23 players, most new players, but a few hardened veterans. <br />
<br />
Game 1 vs. Eric Hammond&#8217;s Gandalf Fellowship/Isengard Orcs<br />
	Eric is one of the veteran players and I thought it was a little weird that I got paired with him first round.  Eric is also one of the funnest guys to play the rings with.  He is also and invited member of my birthday party.  This was the one deck I didn&#8217;t want to play, I had seen Eric tweaking his deck and knew it was Isengard orcs, which can hurt a big fellowhip. I know Eric doesn&#8217;t bid high so I bid three to his zero and my green dragon comes out.  I get out four guys right away and sting, and scan his hand, he has two orcs, one of them a smith, I take the extra exertions so he can&#8217;t get the smith out.  I am very worried about losing sting.  He puts down a guy who wins and does some wounds, I move on again knowing he still can&#8217;t get the smith out.  On Eric&#8217;s turn he drops Aragorn and moves. I get out a big Uruk and he stops on 2.  Site four I put down some more characters and sting again.  He has an overseer and the smith. I sting it so he can only get one out, he chooses the overseer.  I still haven&#8217;t got Lego or servants or weapons, save sting, so I can&#8217;t beat the overseer and he exhausts gandy.  At site five I scan his hand, and he has like two orcs, but no enquea.  I put out my sixth companion and roll, giving him Sam at that point and moving confidently on to six. He moves one time at site four and stops.  I drop my remaining characters, going up to eight companions, and easily move to eight. Eric says theres not much he can do.  He makes his single move again and I roll to nine.  He puts down four orcs, including an overseer and commander, but all he can do is give me about nine wounds, two of his guys then die to archery, and he shakes my hand. <br />
FW +3<br />
Highs: Beating Isengard orcs, and never having problems with the smith.  Playing with Eric. <br />
Lows: I felt bad rolling over Eric, our games are usually a lot closer. <br />
<br />
Game 2 vs. Randy Simons Horn/Moria Swarm<br />
	Randy is prlly the best player at the tourney, and I cant believe I have to play him second round. I go first and he plays an orc on me at site 2.  I have not drawn any major companions, and my theory is never move into moria unless your set up.  So I stop.  Randy takes this as an opportunity to jump.  Which I am glad for, one of my big problems when running uruks is that I draw all shadow hands, and this was no exception. Randy moves to Hollin with like Aragorn, Boromir, and Lego.  They get beat up pretty bad.  Ive been scanning Randys hand and he&#8217;s holding it, waiting for me to put down and elf (he has a few scouts), in the end this is one of the things that kills him, moria has to cycle. But he wants a beat down.  So, he puts nothing down on four, I decide to move on after I sting out the pool.  He gets one orc and rog down on site five.  Randy has a few site six allies up so he thinks he&#8217;s gonna be alright double moving.  He goes to the bridge and faces a few uruks, but is able to handle them and then moves on, thinking he can sack an exhausted celeborn.  I have a troop out, and can either get out Saruman, which gorn can take an Uruk twice, or tower assassin.  I opt the assassin and kill celeborn. This in turn costs him Boromir, cause he&#8217;s running horn, and really hurts him.  He could have sacked orophin, but I think he wanted to keep him for my uruks (not knowing of course confluence was coming up.  I have arwen in my hand and am debating putting her down. He can&#8217;t get that huge of a swarm now, right?  I drop her and Thrarin moving to galadriels glade.  He drops seven orcs, to my six, including Thrarin.  I&#8217;m like, geez I&#8217;m done.  Then I&#8217;m glad that I didn&#8217;t sack Sam to the rog. Frodo is overwhelmed and Sam takes the ring.  Randy drops two more elven allies and moves.  The confluence gets rid of them all, and my uruks mess him up.  At site eight he sees one of my 4  old men and Aragorn is killed off, and then Frodo is overwhelmed. <br />
FW +6<br />
Highs: Sam saving the day.  <br />
Lows: Forgetting what a few orc scouts can do when an elf is down!  <br />
<br />
Game 3 vs. Chris Goodwins Mixed Minions (mostly Nazgul)<br />
	Chris has beaten me before, he has this huge deck, but seems to get the gosh darnitdest luck against me!  I mean, most people can&#8217;t win with an 80-card nazi deck.  So, I bid one to his zero and make him go first. He sets up and is off.  I don&#8217;t do much to him, I have a horrible draw as usual, and he goes to three.  I get Gorn, Boromir and Merry, and figure I&#8217;m all-good.  But he gets out Attea, blade and has four pool left.  I have no servants or anything, so I figure I&#8217;m gonna kill Boromir and merry, but I can at least save Boromir if I use merry, maybe.  But I screw up and o merry first and the son of Denethor also perishes.  It&#8217;s at this point that I realize I have to win with my dark.  He only has Aragorn and maybe one other companion but he&#8217;s got no strangers and choke going.  I still haven&#8217;t done much to him even when he gets to six, but he is having problems getting people.  When he starts six he drops Gandalf so I have another big boy to worry about, but has no sting.  On site eight I have a choice. I have enough pool to get down the old man and three uruks, or four uruks.  He has four guys, I opt for the uruks.  He notices were at the foot and says like dammit. Sure enough, he had a valiant man in his hand, and like three pumps, see what I mean, amazing luck against me, thank the gods for the foot!!!! He has nothing for Frodo and the game ends.<br />
FW +9 <br />
Highs: Getting my revenge at the foot!<br />
Lows: Not being smart about dealing with his Attea. <br />
<br />
Game 4 vs. Chris Hahs&#8217; Gorn/ Uruks<br />
	Chris Hahs was always fun to play  the wars with and I have a good time playing rings with him as well. I decide to just have fun and make some jokes about Sam and frodo&#8217;s relationship.  Chris laughs, and I know it&#8217;ll be a good game, but the pressure is on.  Once again I bid one to his zero and he says, &#8220;it&#8217;s the pony right?&#8221; and I&#8217;m like, &#8220;nope, green dragon&#8221;, he looks nervous and starts with Aragorn (later I would find that he normally starts with Gandalf).  I stop at two as he gets down  like two or three big guys on me.  He does the double jump to three and moves in the lead.  He, however is having problems drawing companions.  I manage to stop him at 4 as I move up to three.  I get out two guys and the old man, kill on of his companions and he stealths with Frodo to save wounds. He&#8217;s down to Aragorn and Frodo  I move into four and am alright.  He moves to five and I decided to go with the Balrog.  The rog kills Aragorn, I bet he was wishing he saved that stealth.  He moves into six with just Frodo and filibert.  I drop a captain and he shakes my hand, having nothing.  He showed me his hand, which was filled with Gandalf stuff.  I had to get Aragorn though, so I wouldn&#8217;t be stuck with men stuff he says.  I told him it was a tough call, but he should run more than (I think one) Aragorn, you can t count on the pony. <br />
FW +12<br />
Highs: Screwing him with the Green Dragon<br />
Lows: See below!<br />
<br />
My family is prone to anxiety attacks. I don&#8217;t get them usually when I&#8217;m in a tourney, or gaming in general, but I got a massive one after the fourth game, I finished it in under 20 minutes and I think the wait was just too much for me. I felt like I was gonna pass out, my head was throbbing, and I was having problems breathing.  I went outside and tried to get air to deal with it, when the pairing were finally called I hoped I would make it through the game, but  when I sat down with norm I went into play mode and forgot the attack. <br />
<br />
Game 5 vs. Norm Lao&#8217;s Gorn/Uruks<br />
	Norm is a good friend and fellow rider, and I hadn&#8217;t played him in while and it was good to. I felt like I was destined to go 5-0, I mean it was my bday, I had a great deck, who could stop me.  I bid one to norms zero and he says, can I change my starting fellowship, I say sure.  He starts with Heir to the White City and that&#8217;s it.  I draw nothing as well, my hand is all shadow, BIG shadow like Lurtz and troops.  I stopped at two and started tossing away shadow cards.  Norms luck was the same as mine. He just moves after playing Sam.  I give him the site and he stops, we are both just throwing away shadow cards.  By four I have a few guys, including Boromir, so I feel a little safe going into five.  When he moves to five I drop rog which does a measly two wounds to Aragorn.  This game is sucking for both of us, and we are crawling. At five I drop gorn and move to six, knowing that norm has one savagery but that gorn with armor is gonna be fine.  Ive finally got a servant. So we make it there and all&#8217;s well.  Norm moves into six with his two guys as well.  Norm stops me at seven. He gets Gandalf at six and moves.  I drop a squad on him finally and he stops.  At seven I have Boromir, Gandalf, Frodo, gorn and two servants, Thrarin (who I had at six, but was afraid to play fearing confluence.) I move to eight and he gets down two uruks and Saruman.  I am able to beat the uruks down without using any of my cards and exhaust Saruman. Now I have a dilemma, do I take the chance of  a beat down at nine, I don&#8217;t think I can stop him at eight or nine, and Boromir should be able to save Frodo.  So I go, figuring slopes, he plays the tracker site, and I&#8217;m like oh, no. Luckily he only has two trackers and he gets enquea down. So, I win with out having to lose anyone!  And norm shakes my hand. <br />
FW +15<br />
Highs: doing the 8-9 double move against Saruman, sometimes its worth the risk. <br />
Lows: Norm and my deck not coming together at all. <br />
<br />
So that&#8217;s it I win, 5-0, its been too long baby!  Its my birthday and I&#8217;m happy. I get a 50 dollar gift certificate which I quickly use like 20 of to get some wars cards that I&#8217;m missing from my set (any one have endor cards?) and Tru Deau gets a figurine.  The squad didn&#8217;t do so good, TruDeau going 2-3 (I think) and garland going 1-4. But we head out.  I still am a little stressed from the anxiety attack and   so I lay into the beer (red hooks) right away. I cooked steaks, burgers, and dogs for my guests, and we drank and  played until 630am +!  It was a great time!  Thanks to those who showed:<br />
<br />
(dis?)Honor Roll<br />
Mark Evans (steaks, heiny, newcastle), Eric Hammond (Nah dude, it hangs),  Myself, Ted Tschopp (Tea, malt liqueur), Jason Makohon (tables), Dunya Ertan (trash Vomit), Lisa Gansky (Vodka), Mike Garland, Gahret Noda (sink Vomit), Dave Chafin, and Dave Trudeau (shopper).<br />
<br />
Props: <br />
<br />
Mile High for always being good to me!<br />
Ram for running a good tourney. <br />
Birthday luck and a little skill!<br />
All my opponents. <br />
All those who showed to my party!<br />
Trudeau for helping me clean. <br />
<br />
Slops: <br />
Age, it hasn&#8217;t really been 30 years???<br />
All those who didn&#8217;t show to the party!!!<br />
Eric Bruen, the only guy who can keep up with me on the sauce, and he doesn&#8217;t show!<br />
The rest of the party folk for making Trudeau and I clean!<br />
<br />
Thanks everyone for helping me bring in 30 years!<br />
